sub_title: Research Master's Student, Social & Economic Psychology
summary: Interested in utilizing research to understand the underlying behavioral, cognitive, and emotional processes during intergroup interactions, especially between groups in conflict, and marginalized social groups. I aspire to apply knowledge into practice by using behavioral interventions which promote conflict resolution and minority visibility on broader societal but also within work and organizational contexts.
